{
  "texts": [
    "34 While these action sequences contain detailed information for execution, their evaluations focus more on the type of action than the parameters or objects of that action.",
    "SynthReader, 35 a rule-based translator developed by Mehr et al., converts natural language procedures to χDL, a data schema designed for chemical operations.",
    "Such a rule-based method, despite being computationally efficient, has to be expanded/modified to adapt to a different distribution, e.g., a change in writing style.",
    "Various submissions to Cheminformatics Elsevier Melbourne University (ChEMU) evaluation lab [36] [37] [38] also aim to solve the NER/RE tasks including reaction/workup steps.",
    "Since these campaigns aim at evaluating individual NER/RE tasks, they do not constitute an end-to-end solution for structured data extraction into a specific output data schema."
  ]
}